Runs best at 1920 x 1080 resolution.

I had to cut back on some implementations due to time constraints :( .

GRIDiots is a sandbox, taking place in the GPU.
Disassemble some blocks, gain blocks and vertices, build a converter and conver vertices into tris.
You could also convert tris into quads and quads into spheres.

Unfortunately, Turret isn't working, but savespot (Storage) is!
There's one "hidden" recepie, and several non-functioning objects (such as Battery, which was supposed to power devices).

Also you could kill gridiots and get their drop - byte pack.

Controls:
WASD + Spacebar = movement;
LMB = destroy/shoot (select vertex for shooting);
RMB = build;
1-6 = select tool;

Escape = escape.

This is a game about the fear and wonder that comes from exploring the unknown.

